Senior Sourcing Specialist
Responsibilities
As Senior Sourcing Specialist, the incumbent will be responsible to fully support in develop and execute sourcing strategy for the company in systematic state-of-the-art procurement way. The task will be covering, but not limited to :Lead cross functional teams to determinate and evaluate sustainable improvement opportunities toward lowest total cost of OwnershipNegotiate and implement Agreements with preferred suppliersEnsure compliance to contracted agreements with other functions in the Corporate at the company, regional and global level.Review and improve both supplier’s and company’s performance against KPI’s to achieve sustainable lower Total Cost of Ownership.  Bachelor Degree from reputable university, degree in Economic or Engineering (Industrial, Mechanical or Electrical) is preferable.Min 5 years experiences in similar position at any multinational or manufacturing companyMicrosoft Office, SAPGood command in English oral and writtenExcellence procurement and negotiation skillsStrong leadership, problem solving and analytical skillContract drafting and management skillUnderstanding of various process measuring analyzersFlexible approach to managing a wide variety of commodity types( goods and service )
